@NODE prelude
@TITLE "The Prelude"
@{JCENTER}@{LINE}@{B}Prelude@{UB}
@{LINE}
@{CODE}@{JLEFT}
SystemFont is a font and patch package.  The font is a nice 8x8 topaz

replacement.  The patch is a small program that replaces the topaz.font with

systemfont.font.  Also included are a 10pt FIXED and 11pt + 12pt PROPORTIONAL

fonts for the rest of the System Font Preferences...
@ENDNODE

@NODE past
@TITLE "The Past"
@{CODE}@{JLEFT}
Version 1.0  -  Initial release.

Version 1.1  -  Cleaned up the font.

Version 1.2  -  Added 10pt FIXED and 11pt + 12pt PROPORTIONAL fonts.

Version 1.3  -  Cleaned up the fonts.

Version 1.4  -  Corrected the spacing on the PROPORTIONAL fonts that caused
                some GUIs to get messed up.  Also updated the SystemFont
                patch executable, now even smaller!
@ENDNODE

@NODE present
@TITLE "The Present"
@{JCENTER}@{LINE}@{B}To use@{UB}
@{LINE}
@{CODE}@{JLEFT}
Copy the program "SystemFont" to your C drawer...

Copy the font "systemfont.font" to your FONTS drawer...

Add the line "C:SystemFont" to your USER-STARTUP or similar...

SystemFont is self detaching so there is no need to run it into NIL...

Also recommended for Hi-Res screens is setting Font Preferences to:

  Workbench Icon Text:  SystemFontP 11 
  System Default Text:  SystemFont  10
          Screen Text:  SystemFontP 12

...be ready for the new fonts on your next boot!
@ENDNODE

